Package: fastsimplexreg
Type: Package
Title: Fast Simplex Regression with Variable Dispersion
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "José Evandeilton",
           family = "Lopes",
           email = "evandeilton@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: High-performance maximum-likelihood estimation of simplex
    regression models for continuous proportions in the open interval (0, 1),
    following Barndorff-Nielsen and Jorgensen (1991)
    <doi:10.1016/0047-259X(91)90008-P>. Separate submodels for the mean and the
    dispersion are specified through a multi-part 'Formula' interface
    (y ~ x1 + x2 | z1 + z2), with 'logit', 'probit', 'cloglog' and 'neglog'
    links for the mean and a log link for the dispersion. The numerical hot path
    -- log-likelihood, analytic score, a native 'BFGS' optimiser, density,
    random generation, prediction and link inverses -- is implemented in C++
    using 'RcppArmadillo', 'BLAS'/'LAPACK' and optional 'OpenMP' parallelism,
    so that models scale to large data sets. Density, random generation and a
    full set of extractor and prediction methods are provided.
